
// Create a new sandbox

git clone git://github.com/slingmint/repo-name


// Commit changes locally

git commit -a       //note that -a automatically performs a git add, which is needed)

// When cloning from git://, need to setup remote point for https:, as in follows:

git remote -v       // shows the remote points, add a new one to prompt for user/pwd

git remote add ms https://github.com/slingmint/repo-name.git    // "ms" here is just an alias

git remote push ms master


----

alternatively:

git clone https://github.com/slingmint/repo-name.git
git push origin master
git push origin mylocalbranch:nameofbranchtocreateonserver     //when using branch

